I have been making this dish since 1992. It has always been a big hit at home or any party I have brought it to. I make mine with 1lb of 16- 20 count shrimp and 1 lb of fresh u10 sea scallops (big ones). I use 1 and 1/2 T of Creole instead of 2T, 1/3 C evoo and add a splash of granulated garlic. I also try to prepare it the morning I am going to bake it. Bring to room temp and then bake for 4 mins.. flip and bake for 4 more. Don't over cook or it will be tough. It continues to cook in the pan. Make sure you have some crusty french bread warmed for dipping. Yum!! Also don't convection oven cook it. It comes out better if you just use your regular bake setting.

