This recipe is almost identical to a recipe that I have been making from Joy of Cooking. Combine the juice of 2 lemons, ½ c. olive oil, 2 tablespoons low sodium Soy sauce, 2 tablespoons honey, 2 tablespoons Old Bay and ¼ tsp. cayenne pepper. Add 2 lbs. cleaned shrimp, marinate for 1 hour and bake in a 450 degree oven for 1 hour. Mix 1 teaspoon lemon zest and one tablespoon parsely and sprikle over shrimp. The resusts are wonderful!

