Rating: 3
Very nice accompaniment to grilled fillet mignon. I used 1/4 c. each of olive oil and butter. Also tossed in cloves of mashed roasted garlic. I prefer not shelling the shrimp and sauteed them on the cooktop rather than baking, for more control of cooking. Added the parsley during last few seconds of cooking for a nicer presentation. Could probably cut down on the Cajun/Creole seasoning for more of a balanced flavor.

Rating: 3
I didn't have any cayenne pepper so substituted tabasco, it worked great. Served it with orzo and a salad and it was a wonderful quick meal.

