I used this recipe in a Cajun Cooking Recipe Contest. I had to prepare it at a radio station on a Coleman stove. It works just as well pan frying everything as baking it. It was a big hit! The juice is so good with French bread to soak it up with. Could be used as an appetizer or as a main dish. I think it would be delicious over pasta but would double the sauce portion.

